# <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pytest-dev/pytest/main/doc/en/img/pytest_logo_curves.svg" alt="pytest" height="40" /> Pytest Report


![Coverage](https://img.shields.io/badge/Coverage-{{ "%.0f"|format(coverage) }}%25-{{ 'red' if coverage < threshold else 'brightgreen' }})

![Tests](https://img.shields.io/badge/Tests-{{ tests }}-blue)![Failures](https://img.shields.io/badge/Failures-{{ failed }}-{{ "red" if failed > 0 else "brightgreen" }})![Skipped](https://img.shields.io/badge/Skipped-{{ skipped }}-lightgrey)

---

{% if failures and failures|length > 0 %}
<details>
<summary>❌ Failed tests ({{ failures|length }})</summary>

| Test | Message |
|:-----|:--------|
{% for f in failures -%}
| `{{ f.nodeid }}` | {{ f.message | replace("\n", " ") }} |
{% endfor %}
</details>
{% endif %}

{% if under_files and under_files|length > 0 %}
<details>
<summary>⚠️ Files below coverage threshold ({{ "%.1f"|format(threshold) }}%)</summary>

| File | Coverage | Missing lines |
|:-----|---------:|:--------------|
{% for fc in under_files -%}
| `{{ fc.path }}` | {{ "%.2f"|format(fc.percent) }}% | {{ (fc.missing_lines | join(", ")) if fc.missing_lines else "—" }} |
{% endfor %}
</details>
{% endif %}
